Quote:  A whaleboat ... soon boarded us; and the `headsman', or commander of the boat, piloted us ... . 1845 ibid. 1-123  ... the `headsmen' or leaders had less trouble in keeping their parties together. 1845 ibid 1/317 The [whalers] are enrolled under three denominations: headsman boat steerer and common man. The headsman is ... the commander of the boat; and his place is at the helm except during the moment of killing the whale, which task falls to his lot.
